+	 *
+	 * Forcing cooperative single-CPU operation — the pre-SMP scheduling mode
+	 * already exercised all through boot — removes the concurrency that
+	 * triggers the race. pc's Linux is a terminal and needs no SMP
+	 * parallelism. user_cpus is left for release_thread()'s bookkeeping.
